## 
## Click in a column to sort by the corresponding variable.
## To regain use of the VIM GUI and the R console, click outside the plot region.
p_minprice <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(min_price, ..density..)) +
  geom_histogram(color = "white", fill = "gray60") +
  ylab(label = "density") +
  geom_line(stat = "density", size = 1.5)
p_maxprice <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(max_price, ..density..)) +
  geom_histogram(color = "white", fill = "gray60") +
  ylab(label = "density") +
  geom_line(stat = "density", size = 1.5)
p_price <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = min_price, y = max_price)) +
  geom_point()
grid.arrange(p_minprice, p_maxprice, p_price)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

p_screensize <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(screen_size)) +
  geom_histogram(color = "white", fill = "gray60") +
  ylab(label = "total number")
p_screensize_price <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = min_price, y = max_price,
                                                  color = screen_size,
                                                  fill = screen_size)) +
  geom_point()
grid.arrange(p_screensize, p_screensize_price)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

p_pixel <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = pixels_x, y = pixels_y)) +
  stat_bin2d()
p_pixel2 <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = pixels_x, y = pixels_y,
                                             color = screen_surface,
                                             fill = screen_surface)) +
  geom_point()
p_pixel_price <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = min_price, y = max_price,
                                             color = pixels_x * pixels_y,
                                             fill = pixels_x * pixels_y)) +
  geom_point()
grid.arrange(p_pixel,p_pixel2, p_pixel_price)

p_weight <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(weight, ..density..)) +
  geom_histogram(color = "white", fill = "gray60") +
  ylab(label = "density") +
  geom_line(stat = "density", size = 1.5)
p_weight_price <- ggplot(data = data_computer, aes(x = min_price, y = max_price,
                                                       color = weight,
                                                       fill = weight)) +
  geom_point()
grid.arrange(p_weight, p_weight_price)
